n process is likely to take up to 14 days. <br /><br />Of note: During the application period, you will be given instructions that will grant members an opportunity to further get to know you. For example, you are encouraged to join a channel (/tell an officer in game for further information!) so that any opportunities to group with your peers are fully optimized. We look forward to getting to know you!<br /><br /> </font></p><center><font face="Arial" size="3"><font size="4"></font>&nbsp;</font></center><font face="Arial" size="3"> </font><center><font face="Arial" size="3"><font size="4"><a href="/application.aspx">JOIN US!</a></font></font></center><font size="2"><font size="3"><br /></font><font face="Arial" size="3"><br /></font></font><font size="3" face="Arial"><b>NEW MEMBER PROBATION </b><br /> <br /> Now that you've applied to become a member of Halcyon, you should be aware of our probationary measures. The probationary period is an extended chance for the guild to get to know you and you to get to know the guild. It is a crucial part of every applicant's guild experience. During the probationary period, members begin earning DKP to reward raiding participation. To become a full member, three requirements must be met: <br /> </font> <ul> <li><font size="3" face="Arial">You must have accumulated 150 DKP. </font></li><li><font size="3" face="Arial">Your raiding profile must reflect 30 days tagged following your first raid with Halcyon. </font></li><li><font size="3" face="Arial">Your class officer must post in the Advisory Forum so that your peers may review your performance history with Halcyon. </font></li> </ul> <font size="3" face="Arial"> Should you not meet the requirements to request for full member status within 90 days following your join date, you will be subjected to a default quarterly review.</font><font size="2"><font size="3" face="Arial"><br /> </font><br /></font>
							
